# How we work with Claude Code in forgedTechApps projects

This is the **workflow** companion to `.agent-standards.yml` (which holds policy).
Policy says *what good code looks like*; this file says *how to run a session
that produces it*. Drop a copy into any project's `CLAUDE.md` (or include by
reference) and edit project-specific bits.

> **Layered system, in case it's not clear:**
> - **Policy** lives in `.agent-standards.yml`, served by the agent-standards MCP.
>   `extends: forgedtech/org-defaults` flows org-wide rules into every project.
> - **Workflow** lives in this file (`CLAUDE.md`). Read at session start.
> - **Principles** (cultural guidelines, unenforceable) live in
>   [`agent-standards/templates/PRINCIPLES.md`](../forgedtech/agent-standards/templates/PRINCIPLES.md)
>   — referenced below.
> - **Tooling** lives in `.mcp.json` and `.claude/`. The MCP servers and IDE
>   config that make policy + workflow enforceable.

